  "prompt": "How competitive is the hiring process at Lexmark International?",
  "response": "The hiring process at Lexmark International can vary depending on the specific role and department. Generally, it involves several stages:\n\n1. Initial screening of applications\n2. Phone or video interview\n3. Technical or skills-based assessment\n4. In-person or virtual interviews with hiring managers\n5. Potential final round interviews\n\nThe competitiveness can depend on the position level and number of applicants. Entry-level roles may be less competitive, while specialized technical or management positions could have a more rigorous selection process.\n\nCandidates are typically evaluated on:\n- Relevant skills and experience\n- Technical knowledge\n- Cultural fit\n- Problem-solving abilities\n\nTo improve chances of being hired, candidates should:\n- Tailor resume to the specific job\n- Highlight relevant technical skills\n- Demonstrate knowledge of Lexmark's business\n- Prepare well for interviews\n\nFor the most current and specific information about their hiring process, it's best to check Lexmark's official career website or contact their HR department directly.",
